{"name": "iniconfig", "metadata": {"name": "iniconfig", "version": "2.0.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: POSIX", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": "", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "brain-dead simple config-ini parsing", "upload_time": 1673089689}, "documentation": ["# iniconfig: brain-dead simple parsing of ini files\n\niniconfig is a small and simple INI-file parser module\nhaving a unique set of features:\n\n- maintains order of sections and entries\n- supports multi-line values with or without line-continuations\n- supports \"#\" comments everywhere\n- raises errors with proper line-numbers\n- no bells and whistles like automatic substitutions\n- iniconfig raises an Error if two sections have the same name.\n\nIf you encounter issues or have feature wishes please report them to:\n\n> <https://github.com/RonnyPfannschmidt/iniconfig/issues>\n\n# Basic Example\n\nIf you have an ini file like this:\n\n```ini\n# content of example.ini\n[section1] # comment\nname1=value1  # comment\nname1b=value1,value2  # comment\n\n[section2]\nname2=\n    line1\n    line2\n```\n\nthen you can do:\n\n```pycon\n>>> import iniconfig\n>>> ini = iniconfig.IniConfig(\"example.ini\")\n>>> ini['section1']['name1'] # raises KeyError if not exists\n'value1'\n>>> ini.get('section1', 'name1b', [], lambda x: x.split(\",\"))\n['value1', 'value2']\n>>> ini.get('section1', 'notexist', [], lambda x: x.split(\",\"))\n[]\n>>> [x.name for x in list(ini)]\n['section1', 'section2']\n>>> list(list(ini)[0].items())\n[('name1', 'value1'), ('name1b', 'value1,value2')]\n>>> 'section1' in ini\nTrue\n>>> 'inexistendsection' in ini\nFalse\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "iniconfig.exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "iniconfig.exceptions.ParseError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "iniconfig.exceptions.ParseError.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "lineno", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iniconfig.exceptions.ParseError.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "iniconfig.exceptions.ParseError.path", "type": {"name": "Final", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Final", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iniconfig.exceptions.ParseError.lineno", "type": {"name": "Final", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_extensions.Final", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "iniconfig.exceptions.ParseError.msg", "type": {"name": "Final", "xref": {"fqname": "typing_exte